Import
HuntTheWumpus.fixtures

 Included page: .HuntTheWumpusServer.ScenarioLibrary (edit)
scenario message msg ShouldPrintWhenPlayerMoves direction FromCavern cavern
put player in cavern @cavern
enter command rest
reject message @msg was printed
enter command @direction
ensure message @msg was printed

scenario message msg should print when player approaches object
put @object in cavern 3
message @msg should print when player moves west from cavern 5
message @msg should print when player moves east from cavern 1
message @msg should print when player moves north from cavern 9
message @msg should print when player moves south from cavern 6
When a player moves into a cavern with arrows in it, he automatically picks those arrows up. The games tells the player that he picked up an arrow, and also tells the player how many arrows he has.

Expand All | Collapse All
 Included page: <HuntTheWumpus.DonutMap (edit)
Make map
start end direction
1 2 E
2 3 E
3 4 S
4 5 S
5 6 W
6 7 W
7 8 N
8 1 N

script
put player in cavern 1
set quiver to 0
enter command rest
check message You have no arrows. was printed true
 
put arrow in cavern 2
enter command east
check message You found an arrow. was printed true
check message You have 1 arrow. was printed true
check arrows in cavern 2 0
 
put arrow in cavern 3
enter command east
check message You have 2 arrows. was printed true
